                    <m>11_{16}</m>
                  </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell>
                    <m>18</m>
                  </cell>
                  <cell>
                    <m>12_{16}</m>
                  </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell>
                    <m>19</m>
                  </cell>
                  <cell>
                    <m>13_{16}</m>
                  </cell>
                </row>
                <row bottom="major">
                  <cell>
                    <m>20</m>
                  </cell>
                  <cell>
                    <m>14_{16}</m>
                  </cell>
                </row>
              </tabular>
            </sidebyside>
          </p>
          <p>
            Let's consider the expanded form of <m>14_{16}</m> to see its equivalence to <m>20_{10}</m>:
            <idx><h>conversion</h><h>from hexadecimal</h><h>to decimal</h></idx>
            <md>
              <mrow>
                14_{16} \amp = 1\times16^1+4\times16^0
              </mrow>
              <mrow>
                \amp = 1\times 16+4\times 1
              </mrow>
              <mrow>
                \amp = 16+4
              </mrow>
              <mrow>
                \amp = 20
              </mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
          <example>
            <statement>
              In the number <m>13579BDF_{16}</m>,  in what place are the following digits?
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <m>\ </m>1
                </li>
                <li>
                  <m>\ </m>D
                </li>
                <li>
                  <m>\ </m>F
                </li>
                <li>
                  <m>\ </m>5
                </li>
              </ol>
            </statement>
            <answer>
              <p>
                <ol>
                  <li>
                    <m>\ </m>the <m>16^7</m>s place
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <m>\ </m>the sixteens place
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <m>\ </m>the ones place
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <m>\ </m> the <m>16^5</m>s place
                  </li>
                </ol>
              </p>
            </answer>
          </example>
          <example>
            <statement>
              Write the following numbers in expanded form.  When doing so, replace any letters with their base 10 equivalents.  For example, the expanded form of <m>2C_{16}</m> is <m>2\times16^1+12\times16^0</m>.
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <m>\ A1_{16}</m>
                </li>
                <li>
