                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  <m>\mylnot{p} \myor{} q</m>
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  <m>\conditional</m>
                </cell>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell left="medium" right="medium">
                  0
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  0
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  1
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  1
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  1
                </cell>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell left="medium" right="medium">
                  0
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  1
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  1
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  1
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  1
                </cell>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell left="medium" right="medium">
                  1
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  0
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  0
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  0
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  0
                </cell>
              </row>
              <row bottom="major">
                <cell left="medium" right="medium">
                  1
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  1
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  0
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  1
                </cell>
                <cell right="medium">
                  1
                </cell>
              </row>
            </tabular>
            This means that <q>If Barney is a dog, then Barney has four legs</q> is logically equivalent to <q>Either Barney is not a dog, or Barney has four legs</q>.
            <example xml:id="exmpl-altcond1">
              <statement>
                Consider the conditional <m>\conditional</m>.  Is the converse (<m>\converse</m>) logically equivelant to <m>\mynot{p}\myor q</m>, <m>\mynot{p}\myand q</m>, <m>p\myand\mynot{q}</m>, or <m>p\myand\mynot{q}</m>?
